## Description

@pub-sub-loop-common · P3 · FEA · Claude-E

### Problem

The `common` module supports `async_buffer` — an asynchronous buffer for staging individual state data between host and device. Currently, `async_buffer` requires the caller to manage CUDA streams and synchronization manually:

```cpp
// Current: manual stream management
common::async_buffer<IndividualState> buf(1000);
buf.copy_to_device(host_data, 1000, stream);
cudaStreamSynchronize(stream);  // caller must sync
// Now safe to use buf.device_ptr()
```

The `c2h` (copy-to-host) utility in the common module provides a convenient wrapper for device-to-host copies, but it does **not** support `async_buffer`:

```cpp
// c2h works with raw pointers:
common::c2h(device_ptr, host_vec, count);  // ✓ works

// c2h does NOT work with async_buffer:
common::c2h(async_buf, host_vec, count);   // ✗ compile error
```

### Proposed fix

Add `async_buffer` overloads to `c2h` and its counterpart `h2c` (host-to-copy):

```cpp
namespace common {

// Copy from async_buffer to host vector
// Automatically handles stream synchronization
template <typename T>
void c2h(const async_buffer<T>& src, std::vector<T>& dst, 
         cudaStream_t stream = 0) {
    dst.resize(src.size());
    cudaMemcpyAsync(dst.data(), src.device_ptr(), 
                    src.size() * sizeof(T),
                    cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost, stream);
    cudaStreamSynchronize(stream);
}

// Copy from host vector to async_buffer
template <typename T>
void h2c(const std::vector<T>& src, async_buffer<T>& dst,
         cudaStream_t stream = 0) {
    dst.resize(src.size());
    cudaMemcpyAsync(dst.device_ptr(), src.data(),
                    src.size() * sizeof(T),
                    cudaMemcpyHostToDevice, stream);
    // Note: no sync here — async_buffer tracks its own readiness
    dst.mark_pending(stream);
}

// Copy between two async_buffers (device-to-device)
template <typename T>
void d2d(const async_buffer<T>& src, async_buffer<T>& dst,
         cudaStream_t stream = 0) {
    dst.resize(src.size());
    cudaMemcpyAsync(dst.device_ptr(), src.device_ptr(),
                    src.size() * sizeof(T),
                    cudaMemcpyDeviceToDevice, stream);
    dst.mark_pending(stream);
}

}  // namespace common
```

### Use case in pub/sub-loop

```cpp
// Snapshot individual states for recording/playback
void RecordModule::capture_tick(WorldPartition& partition) {
    common::async_buffer<IndividualState>& world_states = partition.state_buffer();

    // Before: manual, error-prone
    std::vector<IndividualState> snapshot(world_states.size());
    cudaMemcpyAsync(snapshot.data(), world_states.device_ptr(), 
                    world_states.size() * sizeof(IndividualState),
                    cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost, stream_);
    cudaStreamSynchronize(stream_);

    // After: clean one-liner
    std::vector<IndividualState> snapshot;
    common::c2h(world_states, snapshot, stream_);

    recorder_.store_tick(current_tick_, snapshot);
}
```

