## Description

@pub-sub-loop-common · P3 · FEA · Claude-E

### Problem

When individuals produce large state payloads (mesh data, point clouds, sensor recordings), the data must flow from world processing device memory through the transport layer to disk for persistence. The current path is:

```
Device memory (individual state)
  → cudaMemcpy → Host memory (staging buffer)
    → write() → Kernel page cache
      → writeback → Physical disk (NVMe SSD)

Total copies: 3 (device→host, host→page cache, page cache→disk)
```

NVIDIA GPUDirect Storage (GDS / cuFile) enables a direct path that bypasses the CPU and kernel page cache:

```
Device memory (individual state)
  → cuFileWrite → Physical disk (NVMe SSD)

Total copies: 1 (device→disk via DMA)
```

This is critical for the `record` module, which captures full world state snapshots every N ticks. A world with 100,000 individuals at 64KB state each = 6.4GB per snapshot. The 3-copy path takes ~4.2 seconds; the GDS path takes ~1.1 seconds (limited by NVMe bandwidth).

### Proposed API

```cpp
namespace world {

// GPUDirect Storage bindings for individual state persistence
class DirectStorage {
public:
    // Open a file for direct device-to-disk I/O
    // The file must be on a GDS-compatible filesystem (ext4, XFS)
    static DirectStorage open(const std::filesystem::path& path, 
                               OpenMode mode = OpenMode::WRITE);

    // Write individual state directly from device memory to disk
    // No host staging, no page cache — DMA from device to NVMe
    size_t write(const void* device_ptr, size_t bytes, off_t file_offset = -1);

    // Read individual state directly from disk to device memory
    size_t read(void* device_ptr, size_t bytes, off_t file_offset = 0);

    // Async variants — returns immediately, use fence() to wait
    void write_async(const void* device_ptr, size_t bytes, off_t file_offset = -1);
    void read_async(void* device_ptr, size_t bytes, off_t file_offset = 0);
    void fence();  // wait for all async ops to complete

    // Query GDS availability
    static bool is_supported();

    // Batch I/O: write multiple individual states in one operation
    struct IoDescriptor {
        const void* device_ptr;
        size_t bytes;
        off_t file_offset;
    };
    void batch_write(std::span<const IoDescriptor> descriptors);

    ~DirectStorage();  // closes cuFile handle

private:
    CUfileHandle_t handle_;
    int fd_;
};

}  // namespace world
```

### Integration with record module

```cpp
// Record module: snapshot world state using GDS
class WorldRecorder {
public:
    void snapshot(WorldPartition& partition, WorldTick tick) {
        auto path = snapshot_dir_ / fmt::format("tick_{:08d}.bin", tick);

        if (world::DirectStorage::is_supported()) {
            // Fast path: device → NVMe directly
            auto storage = world::DirectStorage::open(path);

            // Write all individual states in one batch
            std::vector<world::DirectStorage::IoDescriptor> descs;
            off_t offset = 0;
            for (auto& individual : partition.individuals()) {
                descs.push_back({
                    .device_ptr = individual.state_device_ptr(),
                    .bytes = individual.state_size(),
                    .file_offset = offset
                });
                offset += individual.state_size();
            }
            storage.batch_write(descs);
        } else {
            // Fallback: traditional host-staged path
            traditional_snapshot(partition, path);
        }
    }
};
```

### Alignment and buffer registration requirements

GDS requires:
- Buffer addresses must be aligned to 4KB (page boundary)
- File offsets must be aligned to 512 bytes (sector boundary)
- Buffers should be registered with `cuFileBufRegister` for best performance

```cpp
// Buffer registration for frequently-used state buffers
class RegisteredStateBuffer {
public:
    RegisteredStateBuffer(void* device_ptr, size_t bytes) 
        : ptr_(device_ptr), size_(bytes) {
        CUfileError_t err = cuFileBufRegister(ptr_, size_, 0);
        if (err.err != CU_FILE_SUCCESS) {
            CYBER_LOG_WARN("GDS buffer registration failed, "
                          "falling back to unregistered I/O");
            registered_ = false;
        } else {
            registered_ = true;
        }
    }

    ~RegisteredStateBuffer() {
        if (registered_) cuFileBufDeregister(ptr_);
    }

private:
    void* ptr_;
    size_t size_;
    bool registered_;
};
```

## Dependencies

- Requires: CUDA 11.4+ with cuFile library (`libcufile.so`)
- Requires: GDS-compatible filesystem and NVMe driver (`nvidia-fs.ko`)
- Used by: `record` module for world state snapshots
- Used by: `data` module for large individual state spill-to-disk
- Graceful fallback when GDS is unavailable

