@pub-sub-loop-common · P3 · FEA · Claude-B

### Problem

The type trait `cyber::std::is_convertible<From, To>` is a wrapper around `std::is_convertible` with additional checks for individual state type safety. It currently has complex SFINAE logic inherited from C++14:

```cpp
// Current: C++14 SFINAE pattern — complex and hard to read
namespace cyber::std {
template <typename From, typename To, typename = void>
struct is_convertible : ::std::false_type {};

template <typename From, typename To>
struct is_convertible<From, To, 
    ::std::void_t<
        decltype(static_cast<To>(::std::declval<From>())),
        ::std::enable_if_t<
            !::std::is_void_v<From> && !::std::is_void_v<To> &&
            (::std::is_base_of_v<IndividualState, From> == 
             ::std::is_base_of_v<IndividualState, To>)
        >
    >> : ::std::true_type {};
}
```

The `is_base_of` check ensures that individual state types can only be converted to other individual state types — preventing accidental conversion of an `IndividualState` to a plain `int` or `float`.

### Proposed simplification

With C++20 concepts, this collapses to:

```cpp
namespace world::std {

// Simplified with C++20 concepts
template <typename From, typename To>
concept is_convertible = 
    ::std::convertible_to<From, To> &&
    // Individual state safety: if From is an IndividualState, To must be too
    ((!is_individual_state_v<From>) || is_individual_state_v<To>);

// Also provide a _v variable template for backward compat
template <typename From, typename To>
inline constexpr bool is_convertible_v = is_convertible<From, To>;

// Helper concept for constraining individual state operations
template <typename T>
concept IndividualStateLike = 
    is_individual_state_v<T> &&
    ::std::is_trivially_copyable_v<T> &&
    requires(T t) {
        { t.individual_id() } -> ::std::same_as<IndividualId>;
        { t.world_tick() } -> ::std::same_as<WorldTick>;
    };

}  // namespace world::std
```

### Usage

```cpp
// Before: verbose SFINAE
template <typename StateT, 
          typename = ::std::enable_if_t<cyber::std::is_convertible<StateT, IndividualState>::value>>
void publish(const StateT& state);

// After: clean concept constraint
template <world::std::IndividualStateLike StateT>
void publish(const StateT& state);
```

## Dependencies

- Part of: namespace consolidation (common PRD #1) — moves from `cyber::std` to `world::std`
- Used by: all channel/transport template functions that accept individual state types
- Requires: C++20 concepts support

## Sub-tasks

1. Rewrite `is_convertible` using C++20 concepts — **P1**
2. Add `IndividualStateLike` concept for richer constraints — **P2**
3. Migrate callers from SFINAE `enable_if` to concept constraints — **P2**
4. Keep C++17 fallback via `is_convertible_v` variable template — **P2**

## Acceptance Criteria

