## Background

In pub/sub-loop, individual state types are often complex template instantiations derived from world topology and pub/sub topic schemas. Writing these types explicitly creates verbose, brittle code that breaks when topic schemas evolve. The `auto(expr)` mechanism allows the world runtime to **automatically deduce the state type** from a given expression—analogous to C++23's `auto(x)` decay-copy idiom applied to individual state declarations.

Currently, `auto(expr)` support is incomplete: it fails for certain composite expressions, iterator-based state accessors, and cross-individual type deduction scenarios. This PR improves coverage and correctness.

## Problem Analysis

### Current Failures

```cpp
// world/individual_state.h

// CASE 1: Fails for composite individual state expressions
auto(encode_state + decode_state)  // ERROR: operator+ not deducible

// CASE 2: Fails for pub/sub topic iterator expressions
auto(topic.begin()->state)         // ERROR: iterator deref type not propagated

// CASE 3: Fails when state is a group-shared cache reference
auto(group_cache[individual_id])   // ERROR: subscript operator ambiguity

// CASE 4: Works correctly (baseline)
auto(individual.current_state())   // OK: direct method return type
```

### Root Cause

The `auto(expr)` deduction path in `world/type_deduction.h` only handles single-individual direct accessors. It does not handle:
1. Binary expressions across sub-individual states (composite individual case)
2. Iterator dereference chains (pub/sub topic traversal)
3. Proxy reference types returned by group-shared cache subscript operators

### Impact

- Developers writing composite individual (transformer = encode + decode) state logic must manually specify verbose types
- Pub/sub topic iteration patterns cannot use `auto(expr)` ergonomics
- Type mismatch bugs emerge when topic schemas change and manual type annotations fall out of sync

## Design

### Extended Type Deduction Engine

```cpp
// world/type_deduction.h
namespace world {

// Primary template: deduces state type from arbitrary expression
template <typename Expr>
struct StateTypeOf {
  // Handles direct state accessors
  using type = std::decay_t<decltype(std::declval<Expr>()())>;
};

// Specialization: binary composite state expressions (e.g., encode_state + decode_state)
template <typename LHS, typename RHS>
struct StateTypeOf<CompositeStateExpr<LHS, RHS>> {
  using type = CompositeState<
    typename StateTypeOf<LHS>::type,
    typename StateTypeOf<RHS>::type
  >;
};

// Specialization: pub/sub topic iterator dereference
template <typename TopicIter>
struct StateTypeOf<IterDerefExpr<TopicIter>> {
  using type = std::decay_t<
    decltype(std::declval<TopicIter>()->state)
  >;
};

// Specialization: group-shared cache subscript
template <typename Cache>
struct StateTypeOf<CacheSubscriptExpr<Cache>> {
  using type = typename Cache::value_type;
};

// Convenience alias
template <typename Expr>
using state_type_of_t = typename StateTypeOf<Expr>::type;

// auto(expr) macro: decays and deduces
#define WORLD_AUTO(expr)   ::world::state_type_of_t<decltype(expr)>

} // namespace world
```

### Usage After Fix

```cpp
// Composite individual (transformer = encode + decode)
auto encode_state = individual_read_state(encode_sub);
auto decode_state = individual_read_state(decode_sub);

// Now works: deduces CompositeState<EncodeState, DecodeState>
WORLD_AUTO(encode_state + decode_state) transformer_state = merge(encode_state, decode_state);

// Pub/sub topic iteration
for (auto it = attention_topic.begin(); it != attention_topic.end(); ++it) {
  // Now works: deduces AttentionState
  WORLD_AUTO(it->state) snapshot = it->state;
  process_attention(snapshot);
}

// Group-shared cache access
auto& cache = individual_group_cache(my_handle);
// Now works: deduces GroupStateCache::value_type
WORLD_AUTO(cache[peer_id]) peer_state = cache[peer_id];
```

### Interaction Protocol: Composite Individual State Merging

```
Transformer Individual
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  encode_sub ──publish──> enc_topic  │
  │  decode_sub ──publish──> dec_topic  │
  │                                     │
  │  merger kernel:                     │
  │    auto enc = read(enc_topic)       │
  │    auto dec = read(dec_topic)       │
  │    WORLD_AUTO(enc+dec) merged = ... │
  │    individual_publish(self, merged) │
  └─────────────────────────────────────┘
           │
    World Pub/Sub Bus (RTPS/DDS)
           │
    Subscribers receive CompositeState<EncodeState,DecodeState>
```

