## Background

The **world_sp** (pub/sub-loop World Runtime) is the central orchestration engine that manages individual lifecycles, pub/sub tick scheduling, DDS/RTPS transport, and world state consensus. Its diagnostics subsystem is responsible for surfacing runtime errors, performance anomalies, and individual interaction failures to operators and developers.

The current diagnostics implementation is monolithic, unstructured, and scattered across multiple runtime modules. Error codes are inconsistent, diagnostic messages lack context about which individual or pub/sub channel caused the issue, and there is no machine-readable structured output for integration with external observability tools (Prometheus, OpenTelemetry, Needle Engine debug overlay).

This RFC refactors world_sp diagnostics into a **layered, structured diagnostics architecture**.

## Problem Analysis

### Current State

```cpp
// Scattered across world_sp internals — no unified interface
void WorldRuntime::tick() {
  if (channel_overflow) {
    fprintf(stderr, "ERROR: channel overflow\n");  // no individual ID, no topic, no timestamp
  }
  if (consensus_timeout) {
    throw std::runtime_error("consensus failed");   // swallowed by caller, no trace
  }
}
```

Problems:
1. **No individual context**: errors don't identify which individual or sub-individual triggered them
2. **No structured format**: free-form strings can't be parsed by monitoring systems
3. **No severity levels**: all errors look the same; no distinction between transient/fatal
4. **No pub/sub channel attribution**: cannot identify which topic/channel caused overflow
5. **Composite individual opacity**: when a transformer individual's encode sub-individual fails, the error doesn't propagate with sub-individual identity

### Impact

- Production incidents take hours to diagnose because individual identity is lost at the error boundary
- Needle Engine debug overlay has no structured data to display individual health
- Cannot set up automated alerts on specific diagnostic categories
- Composite individual debugging is nearly impossible

## Design

### Diagnostic Event Model

```cpp
// world/diagnostics.h
namespace world::diag {

enum class Severity { Trace, Debug, Info, Warn, Error, Fatal };

enum class Category {
  PubSubOverflow,       // pub channel buffer full
  ConsensusTimeout,     // world state consensus failed
  IndividualCrash,      // individual state-update kernel panicked
  TickGateViolation,    // tick scheduled outside allowed window
  SubIndividualFailure, // sub-individual in composite failed
  TransportError,       // DDS/RTPS layer error
  StateCorruption,      // individual state checksum mismatch
};

struct DiagnosticEvent {
  uint64_t          timestamp_ns;
  Severity          severity;
  Category          category;
  IndividualId      individual_id;    // top-level individual
  IndividualId      sub_individual_id; // set for composite individuals
  TopicId           topic_id;         // set for pub/sub errors
  std::string       message;
  std::string       structured_context; // JSON blob for machine parsing
};

// Sink interface: implement to forward to Prometheus, OTel, Needle Engine, etc.
class DiagnosticSink {
public:
  virtual ~DiagnosticSink() = default;
  virtual void on_event(const DiagnosticEvent& event) = 0;
};

// Central emitter — thread-safe, lock-free ring buffer internally
class DiagnosticEmitter {
public:
  void emit(DiagnosticEvent event);
  void register_sink(std::shared_ptr<DiagnosticSink> sink);
  void set_min_severity(Severity min);
};

} // namespace world::diag
```

### Refactored World Runtime Integration

```cpp
// world_sp/runtime.cpp
void WorldRuntime::tick() {
  if (channel_overflow) {
    diag_emitter_.emit({
      .timestamp_ns    = monotonic_now_ns(),
      .severity        = Severity::Error,
      .category        = Category::PubSubOverflow,
      .individual_id   = overflowed_individual_,
      .topic_id        = overflowed_topic_,
      .message         = "Pub channel buffer overflow: subscriber too slow",
      .structured_context = json::object({
        {"buffer_size", channel_buffer_size_},
        {"pending_msgs", pending_count_},
        {"topic_hz", topic_publish_rate_hz_}
      }).dump()
    });
  }
}
```

### Composite Individual Diagnostic Propagation

```
Transformer Individual (id: ind_007)
  ├── Encode Sub-Individual (id: ind_007::encode)
  │     └── FAIL: StateCorruption
  │           sub_individual_id = ind_007::encode
  │           individual_id     = ind_007          ← propagated up
  └── Decode Sub-Individual (id: ind_007::decode)
        └── OK

DiagnosticEvent emitted:
  category:         SubIndividualFailure
  individual_id:    ind_007
  sub_individual_id: ind_007::encode
  message:          "Sub-individual state corruption detected"
```

