## Background

In a distributed pub/sub-loop world, **individual nodes** (IPUs running world_sp) may be deployed at different runtime versions across the same world instance. When version mismatches occur—e.g., a transformer individual compiled against world_sp v2.1 connects to a world bus running v2.3—the result can be silent state corruption, incompatible pub/sub message formats, or consensus failures.

`common::WorldCompat` provides **compile-time and runtime version compatibility checks** that validate individual node compatibility before they are allowed to join the world's pub/sub bus. This is the pub/sub-loop equivalent of CUDA's `cudaRuntimeGetVersion` / toolkit compatibility checks.

## Problem Analysis

### Current State

There are no systematic compatibility checks at individual node startup. Nodes join the world bus regardless of version compatibility, leading to:

```
[world_sp] WARNING: individual ind_007 joined with incompatible state schema v1.4
  → pub/sub messages silently malformed
  → consensus engine producing incorrect world state snapshots
  → Needle Engine rendering corrupted GLB output
```

### Specific Failure Modes

1. **State schema version mismatch**: encode sub-individual publishes `AttentionState_v2`, decode sub-individual expects `AttentionState_v1` → merge fails silently
2. **Transport protocol version mismatch**: DDS/RTPS serialization format changed between world_sp versions → deserialization errors
3. **Tick scheduler API version mismatch**: individual uses deprecated tick gate API removed in newer runtime
4. **Composite individual version skew**: encode and decode sub-individuals compiled at different world_sp versions within the same composite

### Impact

- Production worlds can be silently corrupted when mixed-version individuals join
- No clear error message directs operators to the version mismatch root cause
- Individual developers cannot detect at compile time if their individual is compatible with the target world runtime

## Design

### WorldCompat API

```cpp
// common/world_compat.h
namespace common {

// Semantic version of the pub/sub-loop world runtime
struct WorldVersion {
  uint16_t major;
  uint16_t minor;
  uint16_t patch;

  constexpr bool operator==(const WorldVersion&) const = default;
  constexpr bool operator<(const WorldVersion& o) const {
    return std::tie(major, minor, patch) < std::tie(o.major, o.minor, o.patch);
  }
};

// Version this individual was compiled against (compile-time constant)
inline constexpr WorldVersion WORLD_COMPILED_VERSION = {
  WORLD_SP_VERSION_MAJOR,
  WORLD_SP_VERSION_MINOR,
  WORLD_SP_VERSION_PATCH
};

// Compatibility policy
enum class CompatPolicy {
  Exact,          // major.minor.patch must match exactly
  MinorCompat,    // same major, compiled_minor <= runtime_minor (default)
  MajorCompat,    // same major only
};

struct WorldCompatResult {
  bool compatible;
  std::string reason;  // human-readable explanation if not compatible
};

// Runtime check: call at individual node startup before joining world bus
WorldCompatResult check_world_compat(
  WorldVersion runtime_version,
  CompatPolicy policy = CompatPolicy::MinorCompat
);

// Compile-time check: static_assert in individual's init code
template <uint16_t RequiredMajor, uint16_t MinRequiredMinor>
constexpr void static_assert_world_compat() {
  static_assert(
    WORLD_COMPILED_VERSION.major == RequiredMajor &&
    WORLD_COMPILED_VERSION.minor >= MinRequiredMinor,
    "Individual compiled against incompatible world_sp version"
  );
}

} // namespace common
```

### Individual Node Startup Validation

```cpp
// In individual node initialization
void TransformerIndividual::on_join_world(WorldBusHandle bus) {
  // Compile-time check: requires world_sp >= 2.1
  common::static_assert_world_compat<2, 1>();

  // Runtime check: verify against actual running world_sp version
  auto result = common::check_world_compat(bus.runtime_version());
  if (!result.compatible) {
    diag_emitter_.emit({
      .severity = Severity::Fatal,
      .category = Category::WorldCompatFailure,
      .message  = "Version incompatibility: " + result.reason
    });
    throw WorldCompatException(result.reason);
  }

  // Sub-individual checks for composite individuals
  encode_sub_.validate_world_compat(bus);
  decode_sub_.validate_world_compat(bus);

  // All checks passed: join pub/sub bus
  bus.register_individual(this);
}
```

### Composite Individual Version Skew Detection

```
Transformer Individual (compiled against world_sp v2.3)
  ├── Encode Sub-Individual (compiled against world_sp v2.3) ✓
  └── Decode Sub-Individual (compiled against world_sp v2.1) ✗ VERSION SKEW

WorldCompat check output:
  FATAL: Composite individual ind_007 has version skew between sub-individuals:
    ind_007::encode → world_sp v2.3
    ind_007::decode → world_sp v2.1
  Sub-individuals within a composite must be compiled at the same world_sp minor version.
```

### Compatibility Matrix

```
Runtime Version | Compiled Version | MinorCompat | MajorCompat | Exact
----------------+------------------+-------------+-------------+-------
v2.3            | v2.3             | ✓           | ✓           | ✓
v2.3            | v2.1             | ✓           | ✓           | ✗
v2.3            | v2.4             | ✗           | ✓           | ✗
v3.0            | v2.3             | ✗           | ✗           | ✗
v2.3            | v1.9             | ✗           | ✗           | ✗
```

