## Background

In pub/sub-loop, **tick-gate dispatch** controls whether an individual processes a pub/sub message on any given world tick. Tick gates use **state-filter predicates**—boolean callables that inspect an individual's current state and decide: should this individual execute its state-update kernel this tick?

Two fundamental predicates are `always_true` (always dispatch) and `always_false` (never dispatch / inhibit). These are used pervasively as:
- Default tick gates during individual initialization (before custom predicates are configured)
- Debug/testing overrides to freeze or unfreeze individual execution
- Building blocks for composite predicates (`always_true` as identity element, `always_false` as zero element)

Currently, `always_true` and `always_false` are **defined inconsistently** across multiple modules (`world_sp/scheduler`, `world/transport`, `collection/filter`) with incompatible signatures, duplicate implementations, and no shared abstraction. This causes predicate composition failures when mixing filters from different modules.

## Problem Analysis

### Current Inconsistency

```cpp
// world_sp/scheduler.h — version A
struct always_dispatch { bool operator()() const { return true; } };
struct never_dispatch  { bool operator()() const { return false; } };

// world/transport.h — version B
constexpr auto always_true_filter  = [](const IndividualState&) { return true; };
constexpr auto always_false_filter = [](const IndividualState&) { return false; };

// collection/filter.h — version C
template<typename State>
struct PassAllFilter { constexpr bool eval(const State&) const { return true; } };
template<typename State>
struct BlockAllFilter { constexpr bool eval(const State&) const { return false; } };
```

### Composition Failure

```cpp
// Trying to compose transport filter with scheduler predicate:
auto combined = compose(always_true_filter, always_dispatch{});
// ERROR: incompatible call signatures — cannot compose lambda with functor
```

### Impact

- Filter composition code requires manual adapter boilerplate for each pair of modules
- `always_true` used in 47 places across 6 modules with 3 different signatures
- Tick-gate dispatch behavior subtly differs depending on which module's predicate is used
- Composite individual tick gates (e.g., "dispatch encode only when decode is idle") cannot be built cleanly

## Design

### Unified Predicate Interface

```cpp
// common/state_filter.h
namespace common {

// Canonical state-filter predicate concept
// A StateFilter is any callable: (const IndividualState&) -> bool
template <typename F, typename State>
concept StateFilter = requires(F f, const State& s) {
  { f(s) } -> std::convertible_to<bool>;
};

// always_true: unconditionally dispatch (identity element for AND-composition)
struct always_true_t {
  template <typename State>
  constexpr bool operator()(const State&) const noexcept { return true; }
};
inline constexpr always_true_t always_true{};

// always_false: unconditionally inhibit (zero element for AND-composition)
struct always_false_t {
  template <typename State>
  constexpr bool operator()(const State&) const noexcept { return false; }
};
inline constexpr always_false_t always_false{};

// Predicate composition helpers
template <StateFilter<S> F, StateFilter<S> G, typename S>
auto and_filter(F f, G g) {
  return [f, g](const S& s) { return f(s) && g(s); };
}

template <StateFilter<S> F, StateFilter<S> G, typename S>
auto or_filter(F f, G g) {
  return [f, g](const S& s) { return f(s) || g(s); };
}

} // namespace common
```

### Tick-Gate Dispatch Integration

```cpp
// world_sp/tick_scheduler.h
namespace world_sp {

template <typename IndividualState, common::StateFilter<IndividualState> Filter>
class TickGate {
  Filter filter_;
public:
  explicit TickGate(Filter f = common::always_true) : filter_(f) {}

  bool should_dispatch(const IndividualState& state) const {
    return filter_(state);
  }
};

} // namespace world_sp
```

### Usage: Composite Individual Tick Coordination

```cpp
// Transformer individual: dispatch decode only when encode has completed
auto encode_done_filter = [](const TransformerState& s) {
  return s.encode_phase == Phase::Complete;
};

// Compose: (always_true AND encode_done_filter) for decode sub-individual
auto decode_gate_filter = common::and_filter(common::always_true, encode_done_filter);

TickGate<TransformerState, decltype(decode_gate_filter)> decode_gate(decode_gate_filter);

// During world tick:
if (decode_gate.should_dispatch(transformer.current_state())) {
  dispatch_individual(decode_sub);
}
```

### Individual Interaction Protocol: Tick-Gate Coordination

```
World Tick N
  │
  ├─ Encode Sub-Individual
  │    tick_gate = always_true → DISPATCH
  │    publishes: EncodeState{phase=Complete}
  │
  ├─ World Pub/Sub Bus delivers EncodeState to Transformer
  │
  └─ Decode Sub-Individual
       tick_gate = and_filter(always_true, encode_done_filter)
       encode_done_filter(TransformerState{encode=Complete}) → TRUE
       → DISPATCH decode kernel

World Tick N+1 (if encode not yet done)
  └─ Decode Sub-Individual
       encode_done_filter(TransformerState{encode=InProgress}) → FALSE
       → INHIBIT decode kernel (blocked by always_false-like result)
```

### Migration: Replace Existing Usages

| Old (module-specific) | New (common::) |
|---|---|
| `always_dispatch{}` | `common::always_true` |
| `never_dispatch{}` | `common::always_false` |
| `always_true_filter` | `common::always_true` |
| `always_false_filter` | `common::always_false` |
| `PassAllFilter<S>{}` | `common::always_true` |
| `BlockAllFilter<S>{}` | `common::always_false` |

