## Background

In pub/sub-loop, an **IndividualPipeline** (`PipelineParallel`) is bound to a specific world processor (IPU) and execution stream at creation time. The stream dictates which IPU receives pub/sub commands and where individual state updates are executed.

A common source of subtle bugs is when user code inadvertently changes the active world processor (e.g., via `world::set_device()`) or switches to a different execution stream, then continues to enqueue pipeline operations. These operations silently execute on the wrong IPU or stream, causing state corruption and non-deterministic world behavior.

This issue adds **runtime assertions** that verify the active world processor and execution stream match the pipeline's bound processor/stream at every pipeline operation entry point.

---

## Problem Analysis

### Current State

```cpp
// IndividualPipeline has no device/stream validation
class IndividualPipeline {
  int  bound_ipu_id_;       // set at construction
  Stream bound_stream_;     // set at construction

  void push(Individual& ind) {
    // NO CHECK: assumes caller is on the right IPU/stream
    stream_.enqueue(ind.state_update_kernel());
  }
};
```

### Failure Scenario

```cpp
// User code: accidentally switches device mid-pipeline
IndividualPipeline pipeline(ipu=0, stream=stream_A);

pipeline.push(individual_1);  // OK: on IPU 0, stream_A

world::set_device(1);         // Oops: now on IPU 1

pipeline.push(individual_2);  // SILENT BUG:
                               // kernel enqueued on IPU 1, stream mismatch
                               // individual_2 state corrupted
                               // world state inconsistency
```

### Why Silent Failures are Dangerous

1. **No immediate crash**: The wrong-IPU kernel may succeed silently, returning garbage state
2. **Delayed detection**: Corruption surfaces cycles later in the pub/sub loop, far from the root cause
3. **Non-deterministic**: Race between correct and corrupted state may flip-flop across runs
4. **World state divergence**: If multiple individuals are affected, the world model loses consistency

### Current Workaround (Insufficient)

Callers are expected to read documentation and manually ensure device/stream consistency. In practice this is error-prone, especially in Python bindings where device management is less explicit.

---

## Proposed Design

### Assertion Macro

```cpp
// world/std/pipeline/assertions.h
namespace world::std::pipeline {

// Debug-mode assertion (compiled out in release unless WORLD_SAFE_MODE=1)
#if defined(WORLD_DEBUG) || defined(WORLD_SAFE_MODE)
#define WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(pipeline)                           \
  do {                                                                    \
    int active_ipu = world::get_active_device();                          \
    Stream active_stream = world::get_active_stream();                    \
    if (active_ipu != (pipeline).bound_ipu_id()) {                       \
      world::panic(                                                       \
        "IndividualPipeline: active IPU ({}) != bound IPU ({})."        \
        " Did you call world::set_device() after pipeline creation?",    \
        active_ipu, (pipeline).bound_ipu_id()                            \
      );                                                                  \
    }                                                                     \
    if (active_stream != (pipeline).bound_stream()) {                    \
      world::panic(                                                       \
        "IndividualPipeline: active stream ({}) != bound stream ({}).", \
        active_stream.id(), (pipeline).bound_stream().id()               \
      );                                                                  \
    }                                                                     \
  } while(0)
#else
#define WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(pipeline) ((void)0)
#endif

} // namespace world::std::pipeline
```

### Integration Points

```cpp
class IndividualPipeline {
public:
  // All public entry points get the assertion:

  void push(Individual& ind) {
    WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(*this);
    // ... existing implementation ...
  }

  void pop(Individual& ind) {
    WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(*this);
    // ...
  }

  void flush() {
    WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(*this);
    // ...
  }

  void synchronize() {
    WORLD_ASSERT_PIPELINE_CONTEXT(*this);
    // ...
  }

  // Getters (used by assertion macro)
  int    bound_ipu_id() const { return bound_ipu_id_; }
  Stream bound_stream() const { return bound_stream_; }
};
```

### Configurable Assertion Level

| Build Mode | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Debug (`WORLD_DEBUG=1`) | Assertions always active |
| Safe mode (`WORLD_SAFE_MODE=1`) | Assertions active in release |
| Release (default) | Assertions compiled out (zero overhead) |
| Test (`WORLD_TEST=1`) | Assertions always active |

### Python Binding Integration

```python
