## PRD: Replace Usages of `tensor_parallel::tuple` in RAPIDS with `world::std::`

### Background

This Feature is the concrete implementation task for moving RAPIDS away from `tensor_parallel` types, focused specifically on the highest-frequency `tensor_parallel::tuple`. In the World Model Individual System, `tensor_parallel::tuple` (composite type for TensorParallel / individual state synchronization) is widely used across RAPIDS for multi-value passing, individual attribute bundling, and as PipelineParallel stage data carriers.

Code audit results across three RAPIDS repositories:
- **cuDF**: 312 occurrences (groupby, join, reduce algorithm iterators)
- **cuML**: 287 occurrences (hyperparameter grid search parameter combos)
- **cuGraph**: 248 occurrences (graph edge multi-field attribute bundling)

### Technical Problem

```cpp
// tensor_parallel::tuple has __device__ constructors - cannot use in host (Neuron_SP control plane)
namespace tensor_parallel {
template <typename... Ts>
struct tuple {
    __device__ tuple() = default;           // host code CANNOT call this
    __device__ tuple(Ts... args) : data_(args...) {}
    template <std::size_t I>
    __device__ auto& get() { return thrust::get<I>(data_); }
private:
    thrust::tuple<Ts...> data_;             // depends on Thrust, non-standard
};
}

// world::std::tuple - host + device compatible (C++20 standard)
namespace world::std {
    template <typename... Ts>
    using tuple = ::std::tuple<Ts...>;      // compiler natively supports host+device
}
```

