## Description

The pub/sub-loop world model requires a fundamental parallel iteration primitive: the ability to apply a callable (lambda, functor, or free function) to every individual in a world collection, with each IPU processing one individual concurrently. This is the world-model analogue of `neuron.parallel.device_for` (itself derived from `thrust::for_each` / CUB's `DeviceFor`).

Currently, iteration over individual collections is done manually via raw CUDA kernel launches with boilerplate index computation repeated across every module. This leads to:
1. **Inconsistent launch configurations** — different modules use different block sizes, missing the optimal occupancy for the IPU hardware
2. **No cancellation support** — a long-running individual update loop cannot be interrupted when a high-priority world event arrives via DDS/RTPS
3. **No built-in profiling hooks** — the `modules/profiler` cannot attach to ad-hoc kernel launches
4. **No support for croutine suspension** — the `cyber/croutine` cooperative scheduler cannot yield mid-iteration

The absence of `world.parallel.individual_for` forces every module author to reinvent iteration, resulting in a fragmented codebase where the same 20-line boilerplate pattern appears 47 times across modules.

**Current fragmented pattern (repeated 47 times):**
```cpp
// CURRENT: Manual kernel launch in every module
template<typename UpdateFn>
void update_all_individuals_manual(
    IndividualState* d_states,
    size_t num_individuals,
    UpdateFn fn
) {
    // Each module hardcodes different block sizes — inconsistent!
    constexpr int BLOCK_SIZE = 256;  // transport uses 128, scheduler uses 512
    int grid_size = (num_individuals + BLOCK_SIZE - 1) / BLOCK_SIZE;

    // Raw kernel — no profiling, no cancellation, no croutine yield
    raw_update_kernel<<<grid_size, BLOCK_SIZE>>>(d_states, num_individuals, fn);

    // No error handling unification
    cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
    if (err != cudaSuccess) { /* each module handles differently */ }
}
```

**Proposed `world.parallel.individual_for` API:**
```cpp
#include <world/parallel/individual_for.hpp>

namespace world::parallel {

// Config struct — allows caller to tune without knowing hardware details
struct IndividualForConfig {
    int  preferred_ipu_count = 0;    // 0 = auto-select optimal
    bool enable_profiling    = true;  // hook into modules/profiler
    bool allow_croutine_yield = true; // cooperative scheduler integration
    CancellationToken* cancel = nullptr; // nullptr = no cancellation
};

// Primary API: apply Op to each individual [0, num_individuals)
template<typename IndividualIteratorT, typename OpT>
WorldError individual_for(
    IndividualIteratorT  first,
    IndividualIteratorT  last,
    OpT                  op,
    IndividualForConfig  config = {},
    WorldStream          stream = WorldStream::default_stream()
);

// Index-based variant: op receives (index, individual_ref)
template<typename IndividualIteratorT, typename IndexedOpT>
WorldError individual_for_indexed(
    IndividualIteratorT  first,
    IndividualIteratorT  last,
    IndexedOpT           op,
    IndividualForConfig  config = {},
    WorldStream          stream = WorldStream::default_stream()
);

// Bulk variant: op receives a tile (ISG-sized batch) for shared-state optimization
template<typename IndividualIteratorT, typename TileOpT>
WorldError individual_for_tile(
    IndividualIteratorT  first,
    IndividualIteratorT  last,
    TileOpT              op,
    int                  tile_size = 32,  // ISG size
    IndividualForConfig  config = {},
    WorldStream          stream = WorldStream::default_stream()
);

} // namespace world::parallel

// Example: sensor fusion update across all perception individuals
void update_perception_individuals(WorldCollection<PerceptionIndividual>& collection) {
    world::parallel::IndividualForConfig cfg;
    cfg.enable_profiling = true;
    cfg.cancel = world_event_bus.get_priority_cancellation_token();

    auto err = world::parallel::individual_for(
        collection.begin(), collection.end(),
        [=] __device__ (PerceptionIndividual& ind) {
            ind.fuse_lidar_camera();
            ind.update_belief_state();
            ind.publish_state_delta();  // triggers DDS/RTPS pub
        },
        cfg,
        perception_stream
    );

    if (err == WorldError::CANCELLED) {
        world_log("Perception update cancelled by priority event");
    }
}
```

