## Description

The pub/sub-loop world model requires a high-performance primitive to initialize or reset individual state arrays to a uniform value across all individuals simultaneously. This is the world-model equivalent of `neuron.parallel.fill` (derived from `thrust::fill` / CUB `DeviceFill`), hereafter called `world.parallel.individual_fill`.

Currently, individual state initialization is performed either via `cudaMemset` (which only works for byte-uniform values like 0 or 0xFF) or via manual kernel launches that replicate the fill pattern. Neither approach is satisfactory:

- `cudaMemset` cannot initialize floating-point individuals to `1.0f`, `NaN`, or `Infinity` (non-zero-byte patterns)
- `cudaMemset` cannot initialize struct-typed individuals with field-level precision
- Manual fill kernels scattered across modules use different block sizes and lack profiling integration
- There is no typed fill that respects the `IndividualState` layout and its internal pub/sub metadata fields

A critical use case is **world reset between simulation episodes**: when a multi-agent simulation completes one episode and resets for the next, all individual states must be reset to initial conditions atomically within one pub/sub cycle. Without `individual_fill`, this requires multiple passes or a complex host-side loop.

**Broken current approach:**
```cpp
// CURRENT: Multiple broken patterns in use simultaneously

// Pattern 1: cudaMemset — only works for 0
cudaMemset(d_individual_states, 0, num_individuals * sizeof(IndividualState));
// BUG: sets belief_weight to 0.0f instead of 1.0f!
// BUG: sets position to (0,0,0) regardless of spawn point!

// Pattern 2: manual kernel — inconsistent, no profiling
__global__ void reset_individuals_manual(IndividualState* states, size_t n) {
    size_t i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (i < n) {
        states[i].belief_weight = 1.0f;
        states[i].position = float3{0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f};
        states[i].pub_seq_num = 0;
        states[i].sub_filter = SubFilter::ACCEPT_ALL;
        // Forgot to reset: states[i].last_update_cycle!
    }
}
int blocks = (num_individuals + 255) / 256;
reset_individuals_manual<<<blocks, 256>>>(d_states, num_individuals);
```

**Proposed `world.parallel.individual_fill` API:**
```cpp
