## Description

The pub/sub-loop `world.cooperative` module implements cooperative scheduling primitives used by `cyber/croutine` to enable coroutine-style individual state updates — allowing an individual's state processor to yield mid-update when waiting for a DDS/RTPS message, rather than spinning or blocking. This cooperative scheduling is critical for efficient resource utilization in the world runtime.

Currently, `world.cooperative` is only supported on **Linux** (via POSIX `ucontext_t` or `setjmp`/`longjmp` fiber primitives). Windows support is absent, which prevents:
- Running pub/sub-loop world simulations on Windows developer machines
- Using Windows-native Azure VM instances for world-scale simulations
- Integration with Windows-based digital twin platforms (Unity MARS, Unreal Engine) that host the Needle Engine rendering layer

The Windows support gap is non-trivial because:
1. Windows does not provide POSIX `ucontext_t` — the cooperative context-switch mechanism must use `Fiber` API (`CreateFiber`, `SwitchToFiber`, `DeleteFiber`) or Windows Structured Exception Handling (SEH) compatible stack switching
2. Windows SEH and C++ exception interaction with fiber stack switches requires careful ABI handling (`RtlInstallFunctionTableCallback` for x64 exception unwinding)
3. CUDA cooperative groups on Windows have different driver API availability constraints — some `world.cooperative` primitives use `cudaLaunchCooperativeKernel` which requires specific Windows WDDM driver modes

**Current Linux-only implementation:**
```cpp
// CURRENT: world.cooperative — Linux only
#ifdef __linux__
#include <ucontext.h>

struct CroutineContext {
    ucontext_t ctx;
    char*      stack;
    size_t     stack_size;

    void init(CroutineFunc fn, void* arg) {
        getcontext(&ctx);
        ctx.uc_stack.ss_sp   = stack;
        ctx.uc_stack.ss_size = stack_size;
        ctx.uc_link = nullptr;
        makecontext(&ctx, (void(*)())fn, 1, arg);
    }

    void switch_to(CroutineContext& next) {
        swapcontext(&ctx, &next.ctx);
    }
};
#else
#error "world.cooperative only supported on Linux!"  // Windows builds fail here
#endif
```

**Proposed Windows-compatible implementation:**
```cpp
// NEW: world.cooperative with Windows Fiber support
#pragma once

#ifdef _WIN32
#define WIN32_LEAN_AND_MEAN
#include <windows.h>

namespace world::cooperative {

// Windows Fiber-based croutine context
struct CroutineContext {
    LPVOID fiber_handle = nullptr;
    bool   is_main_fiber = false;

    // Initialize as main fiber (converts current thread to fiber)
    void init_main() {
        fiber_handle = ConvertThreadToFiber(nullptr);
        is_main_fiber = true;
    }

    // Initialize as worker croutine fiber
    void init_worker(LPFIBER_START_ROUTINE fn, void* arg, size_t stack_size = 1 * 1024 * 1024) {
        fiber_handle = CreateFiber(stack_size, fn, arg);
        if (!fiber_handle) {
            throw WorldError(WorldErrorCode::CROUTINE_INIT_FAILED,
                "CreateFiber failed: " + std::to_string(GetLastError()));
        }
    }

    // Context switch — SwitchToFiber on Windows, swapcontext on Linux
    void switch_to(CroutineContext& next) {
        SwitchToFiber(next.fiber_handle);
    }

    ~CroutineContext() {
        if (fiber_handle && !is_main_fiber) {
            DeleteFiber(fiber_handle);
        }
    }
};

// Windows cooperative kernel launch (handles WDDM mode detection)
struct CooperativeKernelLauncher {
    // Detect if Windows driver supports cudaLaunchCooperativeKernel
    static bool is_cooperative_launch_supported() {
        int supports_coop = 0;
        int device = 0;
        cudaGetDevice(&device);
        cudaDeviceGetAttribute(&supports_coop,
            cudaDevAttrCooperativeLaunch, device);
        return supports_coop != 0;
    }

    template<typename KernelFn, typename... Args>
    static cudaError_t launch(KernelFn fn, dim3 grid, dim3 block,
                              size_t shared_mem, cudaStream_t stream,
                              Args&&... args) {
        if (is_cooperative_launch_supported()) {
            void* kernel_args[] = {(void*)&args...};
            return cudaLaunchCooperativeKernel(
                (void*)fn, grid, block, kernel_args, shared_mem, stream);
        } else {
            // Fallback: non-cooperative launch with software barrier
            return launch_with_software_barrier(fn, grid, block, shared_mem, stream,
                                                std::forward<Args>(args)...);
        }
    }
};

} // namespace world::cooperative

#elif defined(__linux__)
// Existing Linux ucontext implementation
#include <ucontext.h>
// ... (existing code)
#endif

// Cross-platform abstraction (same API on both platforms)
namespace world::cooperative {
    using PlatformCroutineContext = CroutineContext;  // same name, different impl
}
```

